Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} to the water and bring back to
the boil.

Add the tagliatelle and cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated)
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until
golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{150%g} and @water{75%ml}
into the bacon pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a colander and pop back in the pan. Drizzle
with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the cooked pasta, @peas{120%g} and
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> Add a splash of water if the sauce is a little thick.

Share the creamy bacon tagliatelle between your #bowls{}.

Top with a handful of @wild rocket{20%g}.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish. Enjoy!